105// Structure packing macro. If we're not using GNUC, it's not fatal. Most compilers naturally pack the on-the-wire
106// structures correctly anyway, so a plain "struct" is usually fine. In the event that structures are not packed
107// correctly, our compile-time assertion checks will catch it and prevent inadvertent generation of non-working code.
108#ifndef packedstruct
109 #if ((__GNUC__ > 2) || ((__GNUC__ == 2) && (__GNUC_MINOR__ >= 9)))
110 #define packedstruct struct __attribute__((__packed__))
111 #define packedunion union __attribute__((__packed__))
112 #else
113 #define packedstruct struct
114 #define packedunion union
115 #endif
116#endif
117
118typedef enum
119{
120 request_op_none = 0, // No request yet received on this connection
121 connection_request = 1, // connected socket via DNSServiceConnect()
122 reg_record_request, // reg/remove record only valid for connected sockets
123 remove_record_request,
124 enumeration_request,
125 reg_service_request,
126 browse_request,
127 resolve_request,
128 query_request,
129 reconfirm_record_request,
130 add_record_request,
131 update_record_request,
132 setdomain_request, // Up to here is in Tiger and B4W 1.0.3
133 getproperty_request, // New in B4W 1.0.4
134 port_mapping_request, // New in Leopard and B4W 2.0
135 addrinfo_request,
136 send_bpf, // New in SL
137 getpid_request,
138 release_request,
139 connection_delegate_request,
140
141 cancel_request = 63
142} request_op_t;
143
144typedef enum
145{
146 enumeration_reply_op = 64,
147 reg_service_reply_op,
148 browse_reply_op,
149 resolve_reply_op,
150 query_reply_op,
151 reg_record_reply_op, // Up to here is in Tiger and B4W 1.0.3
152 getproperty_reply_op, // New in B4W 1.0.4
153 port_mapping_reply_op, // New in Leopard and B4W 2.0
154 addrinfo_reply_op
155} reply_op_t;
156
157#if defined(_WIN64)
158# pragma pack(push,4)
159#endif
160
161// Define context object big enough to hold a 64-bit pointer,
162// to accomodate 64-bit clients communicating with 32-bit daemon.
163// There's no reason for the daemon to ever be a 64-bit process, but its clients might be
164typedef packedunion
165{
166 void *context;
167 uint32_t u32[2];
168} client_context_t;
169
170typedef packedstruct
171{
172 uint32_t version;
173 uint32_t datalen;
174 uint32_t ipc_flags;
175 uint32_t op; // request_op_t or reply_op_t
176 client_context_t client_context; // context passed from client, returned by server in corresponding reply
177 uint32_t reg_index; // identifier for a record registered via DNSServiceRegisterRecord() on a
178 // socket connected by DNSServiceCreateConnection(). Must be unique in the scope of the connection, such that and
179 // index/socket pair uniquely identifies a record. (Used to select records for removal by DNSServiceRemoveRecord())
180} ipc_msg_hdr;
181
182#if defined(_WIN64)
183# pragma pack(pop)
184#endif
185
186// routines to write to and extract data from message buffers.
187// caller responsible for bounds checking.
188// ptr is the address of the pointer to the start of the field.
189// it is advanced to point to the next field, or the end of the message
190
191// Keep these out of the general namespace -- they're only used internally
192// by the library.
193#define put_uint32 __dnssd_ipc_put_uint32
194#define get_uint32 __dnssd_ipc_get_uint32
195#define put_uint16 __dnssd_ipc_put_uint16
196#define get_uint16 __dnssd_ipc_get_uint16
197#define put_string __dnssd_ipc_put_string
198#define get_string __dnssd_ipc_get_string
199#define put_rdata __dnssd_ipc_put_rdata
200#define get_rdata __dnssd_ipc_get_rdata
201#define ConvertHeaderBytes __dnssd_ipc_ConvertHeaderBytes
202
203void put_uint32(const uint32_t l, char **ptr);
204uint32_t get_uint32(const char **ptr, const char *end);
205
206void put_uint16(uint16_t s, char **ptr);
207uint16_t get_uint16(const char **ptr, const char *end);
208
209#define put_flags put_uint32
210#define get_flags get_uint32
211
212#define put_error_code put_uint32
213#define get_error_code get_uint32
214
215int put_string(const char *str, char **ptr);
216int get_string(const char **ptr, const char *const end, char *buffer, int buflen);
217
218void put_rdata(const int rdlen, const unsigned char *rdata, char **ptr);
219const char *get_rdata(const char **ptr, const char *end, int rdlen); // return value is rdata pointed to by *ptr -
220// rdata is not copied from buffer.
221
222void ConvertHeaderBytes(ipc_msg_hdr *hdr);
223
224struct CompileTimeAssertionChecks_dnssd_ipc
225{
226 // Check that the compiler generated our on-the-wire packet format structure definitions
227 // properly packed, without adding padding bytes to align fields on 32-bit or 64-bit boundaries.
228#ifndef __lint__
229 char assert0[(sizeof(client_context_t) == 8) ? 1 : -1];
230 char assert1[(sizeof(ipc_msg_hdr) == 28) ? 1 : -1];
231#endif
232};
